objects.description:
This course is a survey of the Graph Minors project of Robertson and the speaker, and some recent extensions. The main topics are graph path-width and tree-width, and extensions
used for the Graph Minors project; some description of how this is used to solve the k vertex-disjoint paths problem in a graph; containment relations for digraphs, and particularly for tournaments; a recent solution of the k vertex-disjoint directed paths problem in tournaments;
graph well-quasi-ordering, and tournament well-quasi-ordering.
